Supervisor of Inventory Control - PT. CJ Korea Express Indonesia
Supervisor of Inventory Control  -
Supervisor of Inventory Control
Responsibilities
Receive, store, and distribute inventoried equipment to technicians in a safe mannerMaintain warehouse area in a clean, organized and orderly fashionSecure all warehouse assets (equipment, drop materials, tools and supplies) in accordance with established security measures to control overall warehouse integritySafeguard and account for all inventory moving in and out of the warehouseOperate warehouse equipment such as tow motors, dollies, and hand carts in a safe manner in accordance with OSHA regulationsAccount for all RA (returning receivers), swaps and scraps to be palletized and sent back to DNSWork closely with technician and management staff to ensure ample materials are available at all times to support day to day activitiesReport unsafe acts, carelessness and theft to the Warehouse Supervisor immediatelyMust be able to correctly and thoroughly count all inventory itemsResponsible for keep the area outside and around the office free from trash.Accountable for all assets in their location to include fleet, inventory, etc.Properly train warehouse staff.Accountability of warehouse staff.Scheduling for appropriate coverage.Keeping inventory loss within company guidelines Requirements: Minimum education Diploma related the position.Have minimum 5 years of experience in the same position.Master computer (MS.Office, power point).English proficiency is good (7), both oral and written.Have good Attitude, Discipline, honest and target oriented.Understanding of all reporting and flow of Inventory Please send your applicationrecruithr@cj.netOrpost via address to  :Gedung Graha Kirana Lt 2 Unit 201 Jl. Yos Sudarso Kav 88Jakarta Utara POBOX 14350
